Seeking absolute dominion, Umbra unleashed a suffocating gale, sealing the vibrant earth beneath a suffocating crust of black ice. Heartbroken to see the mortals shivering and hopeless, Ignis ascended the highest summit. He struck his cosmic anvil, forging a radiant sun-sphere to melt his brother’s frozen grip. 

Enraged by this defiance, Umbra hurled a spear of absolute shadow, shattering the sun-sphere into thousands of glowing splinters. He laughed as the radiant shards rained down, sinking deep into the frozen, barren earth, believing the light was forever extinguished. 

But the collision of pure dawn and absolute frost sparked a resilient magic. Beneath the soil, the shards did not die. Encased in stone to protect their warmth, they crystallized into pulsing, golden stones. These were the world’s first geodes, hidden treasures of light offering mortals eternal warmth deep within the frozen, dark world.

