Myth: Long before the seasons turned, the world was ruled by two celestial sisters: Solis, the weaver of liquid gold, and Luma, the architect of bitter frost. For ages, they shared the earth, but Luma grew jealous of mortals who rejoiced only in Solis’s warmth. Seeking total dominion, Luma unleashed a suffocating gale, burying the vibrant world under a blanket of unending black ice.

Heartbroken to see mortals shivering in the icy dark, Solis carried her golden loom to the highest peak. She began spinning threads of crystallized sunlight, hoping to weave a radiant net to melt her sister’s frozen grip. Enraged by this defiance, Luma hurled a spear of absolute cold, shattering Solis’s loom into thousands of glowing splinters. Luma laughed as the radiant shards rained down into the barren, snow-covered forests, believing the light was finally extinguished.

But the collision of pure dawn and absolute frost sparked a resilient magic. As the glowing shards struck the frozen trees, they did not die. They sank into the icy sap, hardening into tear-shaped stones of radiant, eternal heat. These became the world’s first amber gems, offering mortals a piece of captured sunlight to hold back the deepest winter.

